</small><div style="margin-left: 0px; width: 750px; text-align: left;"><br><span style="font-weight: bold; color: black;">About Me</span><br style="color: black;"><small style="color: black;">
</small><div style="margin-left: 40px;"><span style="border-collapse: collapse; color: black;"><span style="border-collapse: separate;">I
am a Ph.D student working with </span></span><a style="color: black;" href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Ewelling">Max Welling</a><span style="border-collapse: collapse; color: black;"><span style="border-collapse: separate;">.
My research interest is large-scale machine learning algorithms,
Bayesian inference, and probabilistic graphical models. My current
focus is to develope online and distributed Bayesian inference
algorithms applied to large scale problems such as topic models,
recommendation systems, and deep learning.<br>
